comments:
I20040128

Up to yesterday I was connecting using extssh to 
  :extssh:dmegert@ottcvs1.ott.oti.com:/home/cvs/plugins
  :extssh:dmegert@ottcvs1.ott.oti.com:/home/cvs/zrheclipse
  :extssh:dmegert@ottcvs1.ott.oti.com:/home/cvs/zrhrep

For some reason it seems that today this is no longer supported by the server
(PSERVER works) or traffic is blocked by the firewall. I tested older Eclipse
versions and they showed the same behavior.


The reason for filing this bug is the unhelpful error dialog which I get:
Unexpected end of stream

Isn't there some other message that could be displayed (e.g. extsssh
authentication not supported). It took me quite some time to recognize this.
First I thought my account expired or got locked caused by a combination of bug
50828 and bug 50744.
